      <section eId="sec_399_YYYY">
        <num>399-YYYY</num>
        <heading>Macrocell renewable energy reporting</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_YYYY__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the company's existing and future investments in renewable energy\nsources, as corporations generally and at macrocell sites specifically;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_YYYY__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the energy demands of existing macrocell sites including any\nanticipated increases to demand at such sites;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_YYYY__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the benefits and challenges of relying on renewable energy to\nprovision wireless service;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_YYYY__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>potential impacts to existing backup power sources; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_YYYY__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>estimated costs relating to using renewable energy to power\nmacrocell sites.\n  2. For purposes of this section, a "macrocell" is a cell in a mobile\nphone network that provides radio coverage served by a high-power cell\nsite (tower, antenna or mast). The "wireless service industry" shall\ninclude wireless carriers, tower companies, and their trade associations\nthat offer service to New York state customers.\n  * NB Repealed December 21, 2026\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
